ai-patthana23.14:0.2_0: under the influence of the Dhamma: the Protector of the Three Worlds
ai-patthana23.14:1.1_0: He doesn’t give rise to unprofitable things. Skillfulness arises in him because of the wrong way.
ai-patthana23.14:1.1_2: There are three more mendicants who have no regrets.
ai-patthana23.14:2.1_0: Not with skillful thoughts, they don’t give rise to a cause of skillful qualities.
ai-patthana23.14:2.1_2: There are three more mendicants who have no regrets.
ai-patthana23.14:3.1_0: he doesn’t give rise to unprofitable teaching; he doesn’t give rise to the cause or reason for causes.
ai-patthana23.14:3.1_2: the five hindrances are not clear.
